It takes too much time to compile offchainState in web worker (does not finished within 5 mins so I give up). I decreased logTotalCapacity to 20 but it does not make much improvements. It does not have manual caching option or anything else.  Here is my configuration:
```ts
export class Devices extends Struct({
  device_1: Field,
  device_2: Field,
  device_3: Field,
  device_4: Field,
}){}

export const offchainState = OffchainState({
  devices: OffchainState.Map(PublicKey, Devices),
  sessions: OffchainState.Map(Field, UInt64),
});
```
I'm not sure if I could split this to one for devices and other for sessions or if I could would it be makes my total performance better.  What should I do to be able to compile it within reasonable time?

In your contract you define offchainState:

```ts
export const offchainState = OffchainState({
  devices: OffchainState.Map(PublicKey, Devices),
  sessions: OffchainState.Map(Field, UInt64),
});
```

And you reference it in the contract:

```ts

  @method
  async settle(proof: StateProof) {
    await offchainState.settle(proof);
  }
```

In your web worker, you import the same offchain state object try to clone it with `Object.create(offchainState)`.  Idk if that will work.

What I think might work is converting the entire `DRM.ts` file into a factory.  Something like

```ts

async function factory() {
  const offchainState = OffchainState(...);

  class DRM extends SmartContract {
    @method async settle() { offchainState.settle }
  }

  return { offchainState, DRM }
}
```

In a test console, I tried this:

```ts
const offchainState2 = Object.create(offchainState);
console.log(offchainState2);
console.log(offchainState);
```

And the output is 

```
